<TITLE> Soldier dies 'mysteriously' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbarhia, May 8 (bdnews24.com)An army soldier died an allegedly unnatural death on Friday while he came home to Neyamatpur of Kashba Upazila of Brahmanbaria on a holiday, police said. Assistant police superintendent Nikulin Chakma of Kashba-Nabinagar circle told bdnews24.com Friday the body of Sergeant Mohammad Billal Hossain was found outside his home in the morning. "Posted in Jessore Cantonment, Billal had come to his village home Thursday night on a vacation." Billal had gone out of his residence at midnight and never came back. His family later found his blood-smeared body. Chakma said police were investigating the 'mysterious' death. The body has been sent to Brahmanbarhia Sadar Hospital for autopsy. bdnews
